<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 1:53PM PDT  by NWS Pendleton</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Umatilla, north central Union and northwestern Wallowa Counties
through 230 PM PDT...
At 153 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tollgate, or 16 miles southeast of Walla Walla, moving east at 35
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Tollgate.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
